#: webmcp-toolkit-pro/webmcp-toolkit-pro.php:182
msgid "WebMCP Toolkit PRO Help & Documentation"
msgstr ""

#: webmcp-toolkit-pro/webmcp-toolkit-pro.php:184
msgid ""
"WebMCP Toolkit PRO helps make your WordPress site easier for AI agents and "
"AI-enabled browsers to understand. Instead of forcing an assistant to guess "
"from the visual page, the plugin exposes clear instructions, structured "
"tools, and form labels that tell the agent what actions are available and "
"how to use them."
msgstr ""

#: webmcp-toolkit-pro/webmcp-toolkit-pro.php:188
msgid "Quick Start"
msgstr ""

#: webmcp-toolkit-pro/webmcp-toolkit-pro.php:190
msgid "Open WebMCP AI in the WordPress dashboard."
msgstr ""

#: webmcp-toolkit-pro/webmcp-toolkit-pro.php:191
msgid "Enable Action Layer to register WebMCP tools on the front end."
msgstr ""

#: webmcp-toolkit-pro/webmcp-toolkit-pro.php:192
msgid ""
"Enable Declarative Forms if you want search, comments, contact forms, and "
"other forms labeled for AI agents."
msgstr ""

#: webmcp-toolkit-pro/webmcp-toolkit-pro.php:193
msgid ""
"Use the AI Persona Wizard to generate instructions that match your site type "
"and tone."
msgstr ""

#: webmcp-toolkit-pro/webmcp-toolkit-pro.php:194
msgid ""
"Save your settings, then visit a public post or page and test it with an AI-"
"enabled browser or WebMCP audit tool."
msgstr ""

